<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-10T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="121" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 811.001/14:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-10T19:00:00+00:00">December 10, 1918—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My December 9, 10 p.m. The Foreign Office desires to receive if possible
                            an advance copy of President <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>’s reply to President <persName corresp="#p_PR1">Poincaré</persName>’s address, also to know whether it will be
                            delivered in French.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>